text: Maipú Partido is a partido in the east-central part of Buenos Aires Province in Argentina. The provincial subdivision has a population of about 10,000 inhabitants in an area of , and its capital city is Maipú. ==Economy== The economy of Maipú Partido is dominated by agriculture, the mainstays of the agricultural production being arable crops, cattle, and dairy products. ==Settlements== *Maipú (capital) *Las Armas *Monsalvo *Santo Domingo *Segurola Category:1878 establishments in Argentina Category:Partidos of Buenos Aires Province
